HDFS: Hadoop Distributed File System.

Features:
Highly fault-tolerant
deploy in low-cost machine (commodity hardware)
design for batch process

NameNode:
manage the metadate(data about data) and path to data etc.
Master and slave architecture. Use logs to sync.

DataNode:
Store the files.

Block:
Files are saved into blocks. Blocks has the same size limit, eg. 128m.
Files will be spilt into different blocks if it exceeds the limit.
Block is not shared among different files. Each block is independently replicated at multiple datanode.